hree business segments tools  storage security and industrial the tools  storage segment is comprised of the power tools and hand tools  storage businesses the security segment includes convergent security solutions and mechanical access solutions businesses the industrial segment encompass of the engineered fastening and infrastructure businesses the company was founded by frederick t stanley in  and is headquartered in new britain ct see full profile analyst ratings sell under hold over buy number of ratings  full ratings benzingas top upgrades downgrades for july   jul   at  am et on benzingacom benzingas top upgrades downgrades for april   apr   at  am et on benzingacom benzingas top upgrades downgrades for april   apr   at  am et on benzingacom competitors name chg  market cap lincoln electric holdings inc  b p  f industries inc cl a  m general electric co  b illinois tool works inc  b kennametal inc  b competitor data provided by partner content trending tickers powered by x  baba  dvax  bidu  aks  advanced search stocks columns authors topics no results found video center learn morestoryful a division of news corp which owns marketwatch is a leading social media services company headquartered in dublin ireland storyful combines world class journalism with industryleading technology to discover verify and acquire original content and provide the ontheground sources news and media organizations need to tell the stories that matter to their audience bing places for business bing places for business sign in using your microsoft account work account google account facebook account dont have an account create one stanley black  decker  wikipedia stanley black  decker from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search stanley works redirects here for the factory started by american inventor william stanley see william stanley inventor this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed november  learn how and when to remove this template message stanley black  decker inc type public traded as nyse swk sp  component industry hardware founded   years ago  as the stanley works founder frederick trent stanley s duncan black alonzo g decker headquarters new britain connecticut us key people james m loree ceo products tools hardware security medical equipment revenue us  billion  net income us  mil  number of employees  website stanleyblackanddeckercom stanley black  decker inc formerly known as the stanley works is a fortune  american manufacturer of industrial tools and household hardware and provider of security products and locks headquartered in new britain connecticut stanley black  decker is the result of the merger of stanley works and black  decker on march   contents  history  acquisitions  business segments and brands  construction and doityourself cdiy  power tools  hand tools and storage  fastening and accessories  industrial  industrial and automotive repair iar  engineered fastening  infrastructure  security  convergent security solutions css  mechanical access solutions mas  divested businesses  hardware and home improvement hhi  air compressors and pressure washers  tools  notes  further reading  external links historyedit the company came to existence as a direct result of the  merger of stanleys bolt manufactory founded by frederick trent stanley in  and the stanley rule and level company founded by fredericks cousin henry stanley in  during world war ii stanley works received the armynavy e award for excellence in war production wwii armynavy production award to stanley works presentation program january   in may  the company considered moving its corporate headquarters to bermuda but public and governmental outcry forced management to reconsider the move by august  the company had decided to maintain its incorporation in the united states john f lundgren was elected as chairman and chief executive officer in  replacing john trani a former protégé of jack welch at general electric the hardware  home improvement group including the kwikset weiser baldwin national hardware stanley fanal pfister and ezset brands was acquired by spectrum brands holdings inc on december   acquisitionsedit  stanley works entered the uk market with the acquisition of ja chapman of sheffield england  stanley works acquired north brothers manufacturing company  stanley started operations in australia as stanleytitan when it bought a  share of titan a subsidiary of bhp  stanley works acquired vidmar cabinets  stanleytitan acquired turner tools based in melbourne australia  stanley works acquired mac tools  stanley works purchased proto from ingersoll rand and it becomes stanley proto  stanley works acquired bostitch from textron  stanley works acquired goldblatt and zag industries  acquired sidchrome tool co headquartered in melbourne australia closed plant in  and started to move all tool manufacturing to taiwan whilist sourcing various items from proto in the usa marked as proto on items due to short supply of left over australian made tools being sold out until all manufacturing was up to speed in taiwan  stanley works purchased the chatsworth californiabased monarch mirror door co inc an american manufacturer of sliding and folding mirrordoors  stanley works acquired blick of swindon england a uk integrator of security solutions communication and timemanagement solutions and cst berger  in october stanley works acquired best access systems of indianapolis indiana for  million the acquisition also prompted the creation of a new access controls group for stanley further additions to this new working group included blick  in january stanley announced plans to acquire frisco bay industries ltd a canadian provider of security integration services for  million in december the acquisition of isr solutions inc headquartered in washington dc was announced isr solutions provides the us federal government and commercial customers with access security system services  in january the acquisition of security group inc was announced security group was composed of two primary operating companies sargent  greenleaf inc a manufacturer of locks and safemasters a north american provider of security installation maintenance and repair services an additional acquisition of precision hardware was made in   stanley furthered its corporate assets in the security market by acquiring hsm electronic protection systems after it had been spun off from honeywell in compliance with preemptive securities and exchange commission antitrust rulings in the meantime the company obtained security contracts as the primary contractor to secure three nasa spaceflight centers stanley works also acquired facom  late in the year stanley acquired osi security of chula vista california a provider of batteryoperated wireless lock technology and supplies to government education and healthcare industries  stanley acquired beach toolbox industries headquartered in smith falls ontario canada then closed the plant  in june stanley announced the acquisition of sonitrol which provides security systems that use audio listening devices as the primary means of intrusion detection stanley also acquired xmark corporation which provides radio frequency identification rfid solutions in healthcare environments as of  many of the stanley security services divisions were being integrated under the hsm brand  on november  stanley announced a merger with black  decker the merger was completed on march    in july the company announced the acquisition of crcevans pipeline international crcevans provides total project support for pipeline construction contractors with automatic welding and other pipeline construction specific equipment and personnel  on september  the acquisition of niscayah was complete  on january  the acquisition of lista north america headquartered in holliston massachusetts was completed  on june  the acquisition of powers fasteners headquartered in brewster new york was completed  on june  the acquisition of aeroscout inc headquartered in redwood city california was completed  stanley black  decker announced in october that it acquired the irwin lenox and hilmor tool brands for  billion from newell brands  on january  news reports indicated that it would acquire the craftsman brand from kcd llc a sears holdings subsidiary subsequent reports by bloomberg indicated that the company would pay  million initially an additional  million after three years as well as annual payments on new craftsman sales for  years business segments and brandsedit sources construction and doityourself cdiyedit power toolsedit dewalt – power tools b  d acquired in  guoqiang gq tools china – power tools portercable – power tools b  d acquired in  oldham saw company – circular saw blade and wood router bit products b  d acquired in  black  decker – acquired via merger in  stanley hand tools craftsman hand tools and storageedit pastorino – carpentry and construction hand tools stanley hand tools – carpentry and construction hand tools fastening and accessoriesedit bostitch – fastening tools acquired in  powers fasteners – adhesive and mechanical anchors industrialedit industrial and automotive repair iaredit cribmaster – tool inventory storage tracking and usagevending management expert – industrial and automotive tools facom france – professional tools acquired in  includes britool lista north america – industrial storage acquired in  mac tools – professional tools acquired in  proto – industrial hand tools acquired in  blackhawk – mechanics tools acquired in  sidchrome australianew zealand – mechanics tools acquired in  stanley supply  services – mro products and services formerly contact east and jensen tools renamed in  usag italy – professional tools vidmar – industrial storage acquired in  virax france – plumbing tools acquired in  engineered fasten